Very disappointed in this establishment and their service. We've tried giving this place a few chances but each time we leave disappointed. The food is always good but the service is always a hit or miss. This last time we ordered in from here made me never want to order or dine with Somerset again. We placed an order over the phone and via email with Nicole, the beverage director, for a pick-up meal on Christmas eve. We confirmed with her multiple times that our order would be ready with all the additional items we had requested and were looking forward to a nice meal with our family on a very important night. I get there to pick up the order and we were told our order was never placed, never noted, and we had to wait another hour while a new meal was prepared. The new order was not the original one we had requested and we were charged and missing a few items. I not only missed a huge chunk of time with my family on Christmas Eve, but the food was also  not what we ordered and not good. We solely ordered from here because we wanted the gingerbread tart and we didn't even end up getting it - and over paid. I tried multiple times to call and speak with the manager about the mishap, but my calls were never returned. I've never had this type of experience at any Boka restaurant and will never be going back. Save your money for a place that will provide better food and service at any of their other restaurants.

Moreover, the burger we ordered was raw and fries not the best and finally customer service very poor as well. Our recommendation, stay away, it is a pretty place with low food quality.

It kinda left me dumbfounded; oysters aren't cheap, there were three left and without a question my plate was taken away.  I am still baffled that a waitress would do such a thing! Ultimately 3 oysters weren't enjoyed  ... appetizers still on the table and bang ... my plate was taken away just because it was momentarily empty. This nonsense forces me to give Somerset a low raiting - which is tragic because the food was delicious and the atmosphere great.

I wish there were half-stars on here because a 3.5 is a solid score for this establishment.  And there is only one reason why they did not make a 4.... price for what you get (That said, this is probably the perfect restaurant for a visit during Chicago's restaurant week!). Somerset is north State St.; it occupies the first and second floors of the Viceroy Hotel which also hosts Devereaux on the rooftop. Staff was very attentive, our waiter was knowledgeable about the foods and specials.  Very personable and professional all at the same time! Fantastic seasonal seating outside along State St for people watching and if you get a corner seat, even that can be intimate.  Indoor seating is vast with booths and the bar on the first floor and table seating on the second.  Just a beautifully decorated restaurant and you can tell they paid attention to detail. The food is presented well.  They have an extensive cocktail menu ranging from beer, mixed drinks, specialty drinks, wine and then the $$$ wine.  If you know your wines, they have a eclectic wine list here that you should raise a glass to. Our apps were delish... Oysters and roasted octopus for a cold/hot variation.  Followed buy the main courses of the short ribs and a salmon they had on special.  We sided the entrees with the crispy potatoes and mushrooms as well.  Mind you, each side can feed two so choose accordingly. All said and done, Somerset, I really enjoyed our visit.  You appear to be a staple in this area although surrounded by many other restaurants.  Thank You!  Enjoy Somerset if you have never been, but, expect to pay just a little bit extra.

The fluffiest pancakes that sent me straight to heaven. I only wish we had time to try their dinner menu. Give this hotel restaurant a chance as you won't regret it.
Great vibe, great food.  We went for brunch.  The pastries and coffee were delicious.  The mains were great as well.

Went for the RW 19. I really like the bread they serve! And the hamachi crudo is pretty good. The hanger steak and the caviatelli are salty, have to drink a lot of water. And the budino is okay.  Updates: Not until I had boka did I realiza how good somerset performed! The portion size is generous and the plates are extraordinary.

First timer here. We made reservations for Chicago’s restaurant week and Somerset did not disappoint. A wonderfully thought out 4 course meal that filled me up. I wish I could remember our servers name because she was the best!! Thank you for my birthday wish as well. 10/10
Delicious food. Pleasant and trendy atmosphere!

I had an amazing brunch. Had chicken with french toast. Really cool decor. Price wasn't that bad either, but the patrons were quite well dressed.

I’ve been here twice - for brunch and lunch, both were great. The service is on point. The food is fresh and tastes good. We got the kale dip, the cod fritters, the flatbread, squid ink pasta and the Mediterranean Bass. The flatbread is more like a focaccia, and the Mediterranean Bass seemed a tad smaller on the portion size, but everything tasted pretty good. Chocolate layer cake is great for dessert. The bloody mary here is pretty bomb too!
Good place

Incredible dining experience! Our waiter was great and gave wonderful menu recommendations. Their menu had an abundance of tasty dishes and their wine menu had plenty of good bottles to choose from. The atmosphere was also great!

I didn't even know about this place until my coworkers told me to meet them there, and wow. So tasty! I'm a huge fan of good rolls, and theirs are dense, delicious, and herbed. A lovely change from fluffy rolls. The main dishes and salads are great as well. It's definitely a spot I'll be returning to!

Came for holiday work party mid-day, and it wasn't over crowded. The decor is elegant and mildly eclectic/interesting at same time. Playful. Our waitress was extremely knowledgeable about the menu and the wines. Very impressed. Food was good. Drinks were upscale. We weren't rushed. Valet is tricky on that particular corner, but you just text the number when you're ready for your car, and there it is. Was a lovely time.
Nice brunch menu and spacious location.
Staff is amazing!
Too expensive

Very good service.  Varied menu to please every one.  Sophisticated/stylish space.  Entrees we had the hangar steak, salmon, shirt ribs, pasta with squid and lobster, and roasted brussel sprouts.  All done very well and everyone's liking. …

Gorgeous location, good food and the best service I've had in a long time.  Thank you Somerset staff!

Somerset, located in the glittering Gold Coast neighborhood of Chicago, is located inside of the Viceroy hotel. I met up with a couple of girlfriends on a snowy morning to catch up and enjoy some of the delicious food I had heard so many great things about.  As I entered the restaurant, I felt like I was transported into a country club. The decor and lighting are stunning. The food at Somerset is described as “Approachable American Cuisine” (which I agree with), and they have a nice range of options for brunch.  What I Ate:  Bellini - passionfruit and champagne - YES. Cinnamon Roll - we split this deliciousness between three people and it was the perfect amount! Eggs Benedict w/breakfast potatoes - This was delicious! The salmon was super smoky.
Fabulous food!

Great restaurant, the place is stunning with its high ceilings and the beautifully dimmed lighting, the noise is reasonable for once, and the food is absolutely great. We tried many things but the favorite dishes of our table were definitely the beef tartare as an appetizer, and the dumplings as an entree. You have to get one order of those on your table at least, it is something different from any pasta (or dumplings) you’ve ever tried.  Service was lovely too, and they have an extended wine list, amongst which really amazing red wines.
Loved working here great people
I went on a first date here. No TVs in the evening. Classy place.
Great food and cocktails. Try the kale dip!
I love Somerset. The food is good and the space is beautiful. The rooftop is a bit small, the pool is a waste of space in my opinion, but great views still

Such a beautiful interior that's complimented by tasty, modern American food. The standouts were the smoked beet tartare, short rib mafalde, and duck breast. The so so was the octopus (over cooked) and crispy brussel sprouts (too oily). The Somerset Sundae dessert was a memorable finale too the meal, and easy to share.
Great food and service.  Wonderful for a special occasion
a nice place for lunch

Pretends to be some high class place. Actually it's just a better Fast Food Restaurant but definitely way to much overpriced. Food as well is Fast Food. Bred with so much butter that the wooden plate gets saturated with it. Taste of the ink Tagliatelle with calamari is good but the calamari is swimming in the oil. The service is so fast that the plate gets taken away after your last bite, even before you can put your fork back. That's again perfect fast food 🤔. And the next waiter is ready to bring you the desert menu and if you take no Dessert, the Bill arrives instantly and the table gets cleaned at the same instance. Then you know you have to leave fast.
Good food. Clean
They are amazing wonderful staff and some very good food, will be coming back

The staff is very friendly and helpful. Our waitress was very nice and checked on us a lot to make sure we were doing okay. We had a reservation and when we arrived we waited a while to be seated. If you go there for brunch it’s not a big brunch menu. The breakfast menu and lunch menu are better than the brunch menu. We also sat outside and there were a lot of wasps flying around. If you have never been here before go here for breakfast or lunch. I would not recommend going here for brunch.

I had the chicken + French toast situation. I don’t recall it’s exact title, but it was amazing. I rarely get French toast because I’m not a fan of the egginess that typically comes with it. This one was cooked to perfection. I requested the siracha syrup on the side, but with the brunch volume the request was missed. Fortunately they didn’t drizzle a lot on. I’ll definitely be back.
Great food! Highly recommend the beet tartar
Very good restaurant in a lively neighbourhood of Chicago. The choice of wine is impeccable.

Outstanding, atmosphere, attention to detail, scene, drinks, food and service. Everything is premium. This is as close to NYC as you'll get in Chicago (think NYC  boutique). The rooftop bar is hip and complete with swimming pool. Excellent venue during the summer. Had a great experience and would go back.

My husband I made dinner reservations for our wedding night after having a small ceremony on Navy Pier with Entertainment Cruises. The staff went above and beyond, spoiling us with champagne & dessert! It is now our yearly tradition to celebrate our anniversary!

So...weird one! I have visited this restaurant twice now, once a date, once with friends. First time we had the Beet Tartare, believe me when i say it doesnt get better than this. We also had the steak....below average, tough and chewy with no outstanding flavours. Not impressed. Second time, we came for the chicken but all sold out. Ok fine....opted for the Sea Bass.....great choice! Cooked to perfection with a delicious sauce. So overall.... maybe i need one more go? I shall update.

Everything, and I mean EVERYTHING we ordered was delicious, flavorful, and just damn good. I would definitely recommend this to anyone that wants a really good meal!  Can wait to go back and try more dishes...

Nice place in a posh neighborhood. Food quality is very good. They are very accommodative for special occasions. Wine can be a bit pricey, careful what menu you choose from. Stopped in for a glass of rose with a friend. The bartenders were friendly and conversational. The space is pretty with art deco gold accents.

Somerset is part of the Viceroy hotel and since we just wanted to have a quick breakfast we decided to try this place. There's an outside patio perfect for good weather and a beautiful interior. The breakfast menu is very limited...  Avocado Toast ($14)-3/5 I hate 'gooey' eggs that look/are uncooked. I think a poached egg would have been much better than a sunny side egg when it comes to avocado toast. And who puts carrots...?? The avocado is quite flavorless and needs some salt.  Apple Juice ($5)- 3/5 I love fresh squeezed anything, so of course I had to get the apple juice. This does taste more like water downed cider, but it was still decent. Not the best I've had though.
A bit loud; but fantastic service; good food; and they introduced us to La Colombe.

Gorgeous space for a lazy lunch. Fried chicken sandwich is outstanding but vegetables are seemingly the star here and are prepared extremely well in a variety of ways. Take a tour of the upstairs space if you are able for the insane level of detail
Went for drinks. Service was great, drinks were lovely. A little more expensive than most
Not worth the price tag. Food mediocre. Most expensive drinks in the city that were small or warm. Service across the board was fair at best.
Amazing food. Almost perfect.
Delicious brunch! Also, must try the copper pineapple punch with vodka. Very instagram worthy ;).
Good food and service.

The food and drinks at this restaurant are fantastic! My friend asked for a custom made drink and it was so good. I got the ricotta dumpling with peas and mint sauce. It was amazing. the dumpling melt in your mouth. The portion are good too...not too much, not too little. I definitely want to go back.

I loved this place so much so that had to go back immediately with my husband for seconds. They have a kiwi swizzle cocktail that was incredible. Their short rib was to die for and reasonably priced. Loved it all. They’re dinner rolls are freshly baked and delicious.
great food...slow service but worth the wait
Nice place to have brunch

The atmosphere is amazing. Really attentive staff and gorgeous feel. I met one of pastry chef at a food event a few weeks prior to my visit, and he highly recommend the chocolate croissant and the butter... It was an interesting dynamic but …

UPDATE: 5* I was back here yesterday with some friends for a drink, and I was blown away when they offered the first round of drinks on the house.  When I asked why, they said it was because that I hadn't had the best experience last time and they wanted to make up for it.  What I loved about it, wasn't the free drinks per se (though very much appreciated!), it was that they obviously cared enough to be checking their reviews and then proactively wanted to improve the experience for their guests.  I had no idea that they had read my review, recorded it and even knew that I was there yesterday (I gave them me name when I came in for the table, they weren't GPS tracking me haha!).  I truly was impressed and appreciative of them caring enough to try to improve my experience versus before, which they did!  It's nice but feel it's over rated.  Service was a bit insincere.

16 Jun 2018 This place has great food, atmosphere and service.  Appetizers We started with Smoked Beet tartare. Very memorable with an excellent balance of flavors. It seams to accent different flavors when paired with their crackers or peta style bread. The octopus was an equally pleasant dish. My wife had the Ricotta Dumpling with a pea puree. She was very much impressed with the flavorful light and airy bites.  Entrees My daughter had the Grilled King Salmon which was cooked to perfection. Flavorful and very moist with a wonderful sauce to augment the flavors. I had the Roasted Beef Short Ribs. They were substantive, tender and delectable with well balanced flavors and sauce. My wife had the seared scallops which were perfectly cooked, moist and buttery with a outstanding seared crust.  Deserts We had three, Rhubarb Pavlova, Butterscotch Pudding and a Dark Chocolate Mousse. All were marvelous. If I had to pick one over the others, it would be difficult but would say the Butterscotch noised out the other outstanding deserts.  Service We had a gentleman who spoke clearly, with proper diction and was at a steady cadence for us to follow along without missing details when one speaks to quickly. He added to the enjoyment of the dinner and helped round out the overall experience, well done.  If we lived in Chicago we would be regulars. This is a place to have a great meal. In all, portion size, atmosphere, service was all worth the price to value.  We are Very Happy Campers  P.S. I was informed Somerset is attempting to gain a Michelin Star. I believe with this food they will acquire a star in short order.
Listed as one of the top chicken sandwiches in Chicago - AGREE!!

We had a good time here at Somerset, but they are only getting a 4-star: - Food is great. We all really liked what we ordered: Chicken & Fraffles, Somerset Burger, Breakfast Burger & the Eggs (looked like a shashuka) - Decor is very fancy and looks like a country-club styled diner. - The service was a bit slow and servers seem a bit snobby. This was in line with the other reviews I've read about Somerset.  Otherwise, we had a great time here and would consider coming back just for the food.
One of my favorite restaurants. Great food and service.
